/common/topic/description.value: A basketball player is a person who plays the game of basketball. This type is typically reserved for players at the profession and collegiate level, not recreational players.

A basketball position is a role played by a player on a basketball team. There are physical attributes and related skills associated with the different positions. The 'front court' players (center and forwards) are typically larger and play a more physical game, while the 'back court' players (guards) are typically smaller and faster and focus more on outside shooting.
The team, position and number for the player - if active

A basketball roster position connects a basketball player with a team and a position. This is a compound value type which means it typically doesn't have a display name, nor is it a often a topic in its own right.
the concept type of integers (range?)
A basketball player is a person who plays the game of basketball. This type is typically reserved for players at the profession and collegiate level, not recreational players.

A basketball team is a collection of basketball players comprised of 5 starting players and some number of bench players (usually between 0 and 7) who will substitute at various positions during a game. Basketball teams tracked here are typicallyprofessional or collegiate.

A basketball position is a role played by a player on a basketball team. There are physical attributes and related skills associated with the different positions. The 'front court' players (center and forwards) are typically larger and play a more physical game, while the 'back court' players (guards) are typically smaller and faster and focus more on outside shooting.

Basketball player career stats compile the statistical totals for a basketball player across a career, either professionally or a the collegiate level. Both career averages (displayed as disambiguators) and career totals are captured.
